    "The participants' opinions point towards a future of academic work where AI tools serve not as passive, one-size-fits-all solutions but as dynamic, interactive platforms that require active human engagement for optimal effectiveness.",
    "This suggests a collaborative model where both the AI and the user adapt to each other's capabilities and limitations.",
    "In this model, the AI serves as a highly adaptable tool that can cater to a broad array of academic tasks and individual preferences, while the human user serves as the curator, customising the AI's functions to suit specific needs and ensuring that the output meets academic standards.",
    "Limitations and Future WorkThe limitations of the project present some important caveats that should be considered when interpreting its outcomes.",
    "First and foremost, the small sample size of 10 participants raises questions about the generalisability of the findings."
